.TH "hvterm_raw_put_chars" 9 "hvterm_raw_put_chars" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hvterm_raw_put_chars \- send characters to firmware for given vterm adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hvterm_raw_put_chars
.BI "(uint32_t vtermno "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vtermno" 12
The virtual terminal number.
.IP "buf" 12
The characters to send. Because of the underlying hypercall in
\fBhvc_put_chars\fP, this buffer must be at least 16 bytes long, even if
you are sending fewer chars.
.IP "count" 12
number of chars to send.
